President Obama has nominated three individuals to serve as district court judges: Judge Landya B. McCafferty for the United States District Court for the District of New Hampshire, Justice Brian Morris for the United States District Court for the District of Montana, and Judge Susan P. Watters, also for the United States District Court for the District of Montana. These nominees have distinguished legal careers and are expected to serve with integrity and a commitment to justice. The article provides background information on each nominee, including their previous positions and educational background.